column5: Well we set off this morning at 5am despite the storm that was on the way. After arriving to our spot there was no one in sight, which is really rare considering the place we were fishing ( the photoshopped backgrounds must be working  ). We missed a few because of slush and ice but heres the ones we managed to hook and land.. Mine   Wishin I Was Wishin's bow..  Had a Nasty Lamprey Scar to it...   And my first OFC tournament entry, 27" great lakes trout.    The drive back was terrblie, taking almost 3 hours, atleast 4 cars in the ditch within the first 20 minutes of snow starting to fall !!
Wow, super report.  Nice looking bows there.  Congrats!!  Joey
Some very nice bows there, nice job, nothing better than thinking a spots going to be busy to find out you're the only ones there.
Very nice guys...how much ice and slush is coming down?
Wow guys!!! Great job out there!  Awesome looking pics too...I can only wish for fish as nice as that!!!
Alot of slush and ice, probably why we were alone, gonna wait a few weeks before going back.
NICE JOB BOYZ!!! SURE BEAT MY DAY  LOL
Nice pics  I especially like the backgrounds, very natural, and I have know idea which river it was!
Nice work guys, those sure would be tasty smoked!!  Rob C
thats a couple of nice bows there4 guys WTG...and at least it was worth fighting all that bad weather....cheers
Awesome guys! In order to fish my spot, well lets say Id need an auger, ice is THICK.
Ok Two votes FishFinders       WTG      Ken
